functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

msg.content: What are the capital cities of the seven largest islands in the world?
What are the capital cities of the seven largest islands in the world?

Here are the capital cities of the seven largest islands in the world:

1. Greenland — Nuuk, the capital of Greenland, is the most populous city in the country and is home to almost one-third of the country's population.

2. New Guinea — Unlike Greenland, New Guinea doesn't have its own capital city. New Guinea is politically divided between Indonesia and Papua New Guinea, with its largest city being Port Moresby, which is the capital of Papua New Guinea.

3. Borneo — This island is divided between Malaysia, Brunei, and Indonesia, with no capital city of its own. Its largest city is Kuching, in the Malaysian state of Sarawak.

4. Madagascar — Antananarivo is the capital of Madagascar. It is located in the island's Central Highlands region and is home to more than three million residents.

5. Baffin Island — Iqaluit is the capital of Baffin Island and is located on the south coast of the island.

6. Sumatra — Unlike Baffin Island, Sumatra doesn't have its own capital city. Sumatra is part of Indonesia, and its largest city is Medan, which is also the capital of North Sumatra province.

7. Honshu — Tokyo is the de facto capital of Japan and is located on the island of Honshu.
